Example:
plaintext
Copy
ISBLANK(Account_Number__c)
Add an Error Message (e.g., "Account Number is required").
ğŸš€ Impact:
âœ… Can apply conditional logic (e.g., field required only for specific record types).
âœ… Works in UI, API, Flow, and Triggers.
âŒ Can be bypassed by Apex Trigger (addError can override it).

ğŸ”¹ 4ï¸âƒ£ Using Record Types & Page Layouts
âœ… Best for: Making a field required only for specific Record Types.
âœ… How to Set:

Create different Record Types for the object.
Assign different Page Layouts for each Record Type.
In some layouts, mark the field as required.
ğŸš€ Impact:
âœ… The field is required only for specific Record Types.
âœ… Does not affect API or automation.
âŒ If multiple layouts exist, it can become complex to manage.

ğŸ”¹ 5ï¸âƒ£ Using Flow (Screen Component)
âœ… Best for: Making a field required in a Screen Flow form.
âœ… How to Set:

